1 This bill also updates the definitions of "veteran" and "disabled veteran" to
2 explicitly include individuals who served in a reserve component of any branch of
3 the United States Armed Forces. Additionally, it removes the specific listing of
4 each military branch in favor of a broader reference to the Armed Forces. This
5 change ensures the law remains adaptable by allowing for the seamless inclusion
6 of newly established branches, such as the United States Space Force, without
7 requiring future legislative amendments.
8 Thus, based on the foregoing, the purpose of this Act is to amend 9 CMC
9 § 2116 to update the definitions of "veteran" and "disabled veteran" and to allow
10 valid VICs be used as proof of veteran status when applying for a veteran's license
11 plate. This amendment ensures that eligible veterans can more easily access the
12 benefits and recognition they deserve.
